LIOGRAPHIC ACCESS TO CURRICULUM GUIDES.     CURRICULUM GUIDES ARE AN IMPORTANT AND HEAVILY USED RESOURCE IN EDUCATIONLIBRARIES AND INSTRUCTIONAL MATERIALS CENTRES. GAINING ACCESS TO THESEMATERIALS, HOWEVER, HAS BEEN DIFFICULT AND TIME-CONSUMING, AS MOST CURRICULUMGUIDES HAVE NOT TRADITIONALLY BEEN INDEXED IN A CENTRAL SOURCE. FEARON-PITMANPUBLISHERS INC. HAS ATTEMPTED TO REMEDY THIS SITUATION BY PUBLISHING THECURRICULUM DEVELOPMENT LIBRARY, THE 1ST SET OF WHICH CONTAINED 905 CURRICULUMGUIDES ON MICROFICHE WITH HARD COPY INDEXES. THE PUBLISHER EXPECTS TO PUBLISHTHIS SET ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. THE UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI-ST. LOUIS OWNS THECURRICULUM DEVELOPMENT LIBRARY, AND THE AUTHOR DESCRIBES ITS USE IN THEEDUCATION LIBRARY